                    <item>
                        <gloss type="person" xml:id="UT22084-088-028-99">
                            <term type="translationMain">Ākāśagarbha</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" status="verified" n="1">nam mkha’i snying po </term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" n="1">ནམ་མཁའི་སྙིང་པོ།</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="attestedDictionary">ākāśagarbha</term>
                            <note type="definition">
                                <p>An important bodhisattva whose name means
                                    “essence of space.” He is one of the “eight great close sons”
                                    (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">aṣṭamahopa­putra</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">nye ba’i sras chen brgyad</foreign>).</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="person" xml:id="UT22084-088-028-100">
                            <term type="translationMain">Vairocana</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" status="verified" n="1">rnam par snang mdzad </term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" n="1">རྣམ་པར་སྣང་མཛད།</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="attestedDictionary">vairocana</term>
                            <note type="definition">
                                <p>The name Vairocana, literally, “solar,” is
                                used in some important Mahāyāna sūtras such as <title xml:lang="en">The Stem Array</title> (<ptr target="#UT22084-037-007-7246"/>) and <title xml:lang="en">The Ten Bhūmis</title> (<ptr target="#UT22084-036-002-1921"/>) as an epithet for the Buddha
                                    Śākyamuni. As a distinct tathāgata, Vairocana presides over the
                                    tathāgata family among the five buddha families. </p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
